@startuml Login Authentication Sequence Diagram

!define BLUE_COLOR #4A90E2
!define GREEN_COLOR #7ED321
!define RED_COLOR #D0021B
!define ORANGE_COLOR #F5A623
!define PURPLE_COLOR #9013FE

actor "User" as User BLUE_COLOR
participant "Frontend\nApplication" as Frontend ORANGE_COLOR
participant "Login API\n(/api/login)" as LoginAPI PURPLE_COLOR
participant "Database\n(PostgreSQL)" as Database GREEN_COLOR
participant "bcrypt\nLibrary" as BcryptLib GREEN_COLOR

== User Authentication ==
box "Login Process" #LightBlue
    User -> Frontend: Enter credentials\n(email, password)
    Frontend -> LoginAPI: POST /api/login\n{ email, password }
    activate LoginAPI

    LoginAPI -> Database: Query user by email\ninclude role and permissions
    activate Database
    Database --> LoginAPI: User record with role data
    deactivate Database
    alt User Not Found
        LoginAPI --> Frontend: HTTP 401 "Invalid credentials"
        deactivate LoginAPI
        Frontend --> User: Display "Invalid credentials"
    else User Found
        LoginAPI -> LoginAPI: Verify password with bcrypt.compare()
        alt Password Verification
            LoginAPI -> LoginAPI: Generate UUID session token
            LoginAPI -> Database: Create session record
{ token, user_id }
            activate Database
            Database --> LoginAPI: Session created
            deactivate Database

            LoginAPI --> Frontend: HTTP 200 { user, token }
            deactivate LoginAPI
            Frontend -> Frontend: Store authentication token
            Frontend --> User: Login successful
Redirect to dashboard
        else Password Invalid
            LoginAPI --> Frontend: HTTP 401 "Invalid credentials"
            deactivate LoginAPI
            Frontend --> User: Display "Invalid credentials"
        end alt
    end alt
end box

== Error Handling ==
alt System Error
    LoginAPI --> Frontend: HTTP 500 "Login failed: {error}"
    Frontend -> Frontend: Handle error state
    Frontend --> User: Display "Login failed" message
end alt

== Notes ==
note over Frontend, Database
    **Authentication Flow:**
    - Email-based user identification
    - bcrypt password verification
    - UUID-based session token generation
    - Role and permission inclusion

    **Security Features:**
    - Password hashing with bcrypt
    - Cryptographic comparison prevents timing attacks
    - No plaintext password handling in application

    **bcrypt Integration:**
    - Internal function call within Login API
    - Secure password hash comparison
    - No external service dependency

    **Session Management:**
    - Automatic session creation on login
    - Token returned to frontend for storage
    - Database persistence of active sessions
    - User role and permissions included in response

    **API Response:**
    - Success: { user: {...}, token: "uuid-string" }
    - Error: { message: "Invalid credentials" }
    - System Error: { message: "Login failed: {error}" }
end note

@enduml
